{"id": 232082398, "title": "Recipe: Chicken paprikash with sp\u00e4tzle", "text": "Brown the chicken in butter and remove it from the pot. Saut\u00e9 the diced onions in the same pot. Return the chicken to the pot and add the paprika, water, diced sweet peppers, salt, and pepper. Cover and bring to a boil, then simmer until the chicken is tender (3-4 hours). In a separate bowl, blend the flour, milk, and sour cream. Add the flour mixture to the pot and stir well. Heat gently until the sauce thickens. Serve over sp\u00e4tzle dumplings.", "summary": "Trail Appliances Favourite Family Recipe contest finalist Valerie Mufford shows Joe Fortes' executive chef Wayne Sych how to make her family\u2019s Chicken Paprikash with Spatzle.", "url": "https://globalnews.ca/news/10555408/recipe-chicken-paprikash-with-spatzle/", "image": "https://globalnews.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/family-recipe.jpg?quality=85&strip=all&w=720&h=379&crop=1", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 16:46:45", "author": null, "language": "en", "source_country": "ca", "sentiment": 0.903}